In terms of applications, the fluff pulp market is segmented into hygiene products, absorbent products, and others. Hygiene products, including diapers and sanitary pads, account for a significant portion of the market demand. The healthcare sector, in particular, relies heavily on fluff pulp for the production of absorbent products used in various medical applications. Additionally, the use of fluff pulp in absorbent products such as wet wipes and food pads further diversifies its application scope. The packaging industry also leverages fluff pulp for creating sustainable packaging materials, reflecting the versatility and adaptability of this raw material.

